  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Austrian freelancer visa process involves several government offices and registrations. Non-EU citizens apply for a visa at the Austrian embassy, then complete additional registrations after arrival. EU citizens can skip the visa step but must complete the same business registrations.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Prepare Your Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Write a detailed business plan demonstrating economic benefit to Austria. Gather evidence for points (qualifications, language certificates, work experience). Get criminal record certificate and other documents apostilled and translated into German by certified translators.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Secure Initial Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">For your visa application, you need proof of health insurance. Obtain a confirmation letter from Allianz Care, Cigna Global, or another provider that meets Austrian requirements. This covers you until SVS kicks in after arrival.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply at Austrian Embassy (Non-EU)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Submit your application for the D visa (entry visa) or directly for the residence permit at the Austrian embassy. Processing typically takes 2-4 months. Be prepared to answer questions about your business plan and how your work benefits Austria.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Arrive and Register Residence (Meldezettel)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600"><strong>Critical: Within 3 days of moving into accommodation</strong>, register at the Meldeamt (registration office). Bring your passport and rental contract. This registration is required for everything else—bank accounts, trade license, tax registration.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply for Gewerbeschein (Trade License)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply for your trade license at the Bezirkshauptmannschaft (district authority) or Magistrat (in Vienna). The type of license depends on your activity—some trades are "free" (freie Gewerbe), others require qualifications. Processing takes 1-4 weeks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register with SVS (Social Insurance)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Once your Gewerbeschein is issued, you must register with SVS within one month. Bring your trade license, passport, and Meldezettel. SVS registration triggers your mandatory health, pension, and accident insurance coverage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register with Finanzamt (Tax Office)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Register your business with the local Finanzamt. You'll receive a tax number (Steuernummer) within a few weeks. This is required before you can legally invoice clients. Consider engaging a Steuerberater at this stage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply for Residence Permit (If Not Already Issued)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">If you entered on a D visa, apply for your residence permit at MA 35 (Vienna) or the local Bezirkshauptmannschaft. Bring all registrations, trade license, SVS confirmation, and bank statements. Processing takes 2-4 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">9</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Join Wirtschaftskammer (Chamber of Commerce)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Membership in the Wirtschaftskammer (WKO) is mandatory for most trade license holders. You'll be automatically enrolled when your Gewerbeschein is issued. Fees depend on your trade type and can range from €100-500/year.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-red-800">
        <strong>3-Day Meldezettel Warning:</strong> Austria strictly enforces the 3-day residence registration deadline. Failure to register on time can result in fines and complications with your visa. Prioritize this immediately upon arrival—it's the foundation for all other registrations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

